{"key":"processedPost-13024180","value":{"id":13024180,"first":13023758,"last":13376124,"when":1281328029,"utime":"08/09/10 07:27 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>rustycobwebs said:</b><br />hmm....how hot can this agar be? Obviously you have to hold the bottle so it can't be that hot<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Pretty darned hot.&nbsp; I use a paper towel to protect my latex gloved hands from getting burned when I do this.&nbsp; I'd estimate at around 140F/60C.&nbsp; It cools down pretty fast, and the mushroom mycelium survives, but it 'pasteurizes' the bacteria, knocking it back just long enough for the mushroom mycelium to recover.&nbsp; Be sure to be right there when it pops through the top though, because the bacteria isn't far behind.&nbsp; If there's a LOT of bacteria, use antibiotic agar.&nbsp; Bear in mind, there has to be at least <i>some</i> mushroom mycelium for this to work.<br />RR","title":"Re: agar hot pour","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}